- Minimal fix updated the website lockfile through `npm --prefix website update wrangler`, resolving to `wrangler@4.107.1`, `miniflare@4.20260702.0`, `undici@7.28.0`, `ws@8.21.0`, and `esbuild@0.28.1`.
- Verified: `npm audit --json`, `npm --prefix website audit --json`, `npm --prefix website ls wrangler miniflare undici ws esbuild --all`, `npm test`, and `npm --prefix website run check` all passed after the update.

## SZLKlaws Legal Governance 2026-07-08
- ME/JW/YL/AIF main-path products have all been connected to SZLKlaws legal document APIs in this Solo sequence. SZLKlaws now owns the common seven legal files and standalone product supplements as the legal truth layer; products keep their own user-facing legal UI/routes.
- SZLKlaws commit `a41ceee` adds the authenticated “法律文件 / Legal Files” governance page plus D1-backed version/audit storage in `src/legal-governance.js`. Admins can select product/document/locale, preview source or managed content, save a new draft, and approve a selected version.
- Public headless APIs now prefer the latest approved managed version and fall back to code baseline when no approved version exists or governance storage fails, so drafts do not automatically affect product frontends.
- Verified locally: `node --check`, `corepack pnpm test`, `corepack pnpm run check`, `CLEANUP_QA=1 corepack pnpm run verify:ui`, and a Playwright probe for the legal governance page. GitHub Cloudflare deploy run `28933287526` succeeded; production `/health` and public `/api/legal/document` checks passed. Production admin endpoint was not reverified because the local `.dev.vars` admin password did not authenticate against production.

## ME SEO Follow-up 2026-07-07
- Verified via CloudMCP Google Search Console for `sc-domain:mysticeast.uk`: last ME horoscope SEO optimization was 2026-07-01; as of 2026-07-07 GSC only returned complete data through 2026-07-05, so the available post-change comparison window is 2026-07-01..2026-07-05 versus 2026-06-26..2026-06-30.
- Comparable 5-day site totals changed from 46 clicks / 3,665 impressions before to 52 clicks / 3,281 impressions after; `/en/horoscope` changed from 45 clicks / 2,276 impressions / CTR 1.98% / avg position 8.84 to 50 clicks / 2,687 impressions / CTR 1.86% / avg position 8.59.
- Keyword-level signal: rankings/impressions improved for `chinese horoscope today` and `daily chinese horoscope`, but CTR weakened on some head terms; new/strong click signals appeared for animal-specific terms such as `dragon love horoscope today`, `horse horoscope today`, `dragon horoscope today`, `rat/snake/tiger horoscope today`.
- Current recommendation direction: do not add generic explanatory SEO blocks; if expanding “today horoscope”, add user-facing analysis modules that directly answer search intent, especially love/career/wealth/health/timing/lucky action modules and stronger per-zodiac long-tail landing support.

